/* Vocabulary */ Very doubtful. The word may be used in Amazigh as well, but the tomato is a recent introduction from the Americas. So there's no way of saying that the word went from Amazigh to Arabic rather than the other way round, except in the unlikely case that the word originally meant something else in Amazigh, was then used for tomato, and then borrowed to Arabic.
